Tito's Garage

Overview

Description: Tito's Garage is located in one of the worst neighborhoods in Seattle, Central District, but some of the best work in all of Seattle. The shop is an unassuming little hole in the wall. It’s a one bay garage amongst a series of storefronts. The inside is cluttered. He has part hanging on the walls, several tool boxes open with tools strewn across the garage and his desk area is piled high with paperwork, manuals, pizza boxes, etc. Tito's Garage’s owner, Jorge “Tito" Vargas, was a former gang member. Although he still holds a large influence in the local gang population.
